<body>
    <%- include("../partials/nav.ejs") %>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>About Song Tracker</h1>
        <p>Song Tracker is an application designed to keep track of songs you want to learn and play on your musical instruments.</p>

        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Track songs you want to play next</li>
            <li>Create and manage your profile</li>
            <li>Search for artists and songs</li>
            <li><strong>Tab2Piano</strong> - Convert guitar tablature to piano keys and visualize notes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <p>Register for an account, and start adding songs to your profile. You can organize your music for practice and never forget which songs you wanted to learn.</p>
        
        <h2>Get Started</h2>
        <p><a href="/Register">Register</a> for an account or <a href="/Login">log in</a> if you already have one.</p>
        
        <h2>Tab2Piano Tool</h2>
        <p><a href="/tab2piano">Tab2Piano</a> is a tool that helps you translate guitar tablature notation to piano keys. Simply input the string name and fret number from your guitar tab, and the tool will:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Visualize the corresponding piano key with color highlighting</li>
            <li>Allow you to click piano keys to see guitar tab equivalents</li>
            <li>Support multiple guitar tunings (Standard, Drop D, Open tunings, and more)</li>
            <li>Play audio for each note</li>
            <li>Save your work with local storage for easy reference</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
